Thought to share my experience tonight, copied from Y.  Usually I don't get picky about loyalty rewards, but if different staff are saying different things on different days, well, that is just a misfortune to all their customers. I honestly didn't want to dampen anyone's Friday night, but they could have worked on their "fine print". I basically bought two pokebowls and one large drink on 11/27/2018 for a total of $26.57. I'm sorry to rat you out, but server's name printed on the receipt is Tony. It was a pleasant experience, the ladies at the counter were nice and quick with the order. I also noticed their little message at the cashier how they don't do stamps anymore and that they switched to their check-in based loyalty program. They offered a free small bubble tea as a first reward after signing up. Unfortunately, if I knew that this incident came out the way it did, I would have taken a picture of it, but I did not. I was under the impression that I was able to pick up this "first reward" of mine any time between 11/27/18 to 12/07/18 as per the text I got when I first signed up. When I double checked with the ladies at the front, I asked them if I could pick it up next time since I already ordered a large drink and they said yes. They didn't add anything like "with a purchase" or the sorts to that sentence. So, knowing I had a small bubble tea waiting to be picked up, I didn't think too much about it. Given my location and working hours, I asked a friend if she wanted a bubble tea and she could just pick it up with my number. So she went and was told that she had to purchase something else in order to get that bubble tea. I guess I can understand it from their marketing view and plus they might have expected customers to come back to buy more pokebowls and just wanted a free drink with it but if they were more clear about this SPECIFIC condition on the day I signed up and through the text they sent, I wouldn't be typing this review right now. If anyone signed up for their loyalty program around the same time as I did, the follow-up text says this:  "Welcome to the PokeBowl Station Loyalty Club! Enjoy a FREE Sm. Bubble Tea as your first reward between 11/27/18 and 12/07/18! Thank you VIP!"  Nowhere does it say "with a purchase" and the staff didn't specifically emphasize on that the day I left WITHOUT the bubble tea. All I know is I was allowed to pick it up next time and that I had a short time period to claim this "free reward". So tonight, on the last day of this "free reward", it is left unclaimed. Thank you to the manager tonight who tried to clear this up, but what I got from the phone call was, there are staff who are very clear on the rules and there are staff who aren't, leading to misinformed customers and very rude impressions of Snow & Cream. Thank you for taking the time to clarify the situation with me, Manager, it was not your fault.  Of course, feel free to take a picture of the sign in front of your cashier to show me wrong, but it still doesn't help that your staff and your loyalty program auto text messages don't clarify it either. Fine print goes a long way instead of misleading others about this "first reward". I won't be telling people to stay away from this place, but I certainly won't be telling people to come here anymore.

I love this little poké spot. It's a great environment for friends and family to hang out and eat. The decor and the music are awesome. The poké is always fresh and delicious. Choose from pre-existing bowls on the menu or make your own, choosing a base (ie: sushi rice), proteins (ie: chicken, salmon), toppings (ie: corn, kani, kale), sauces (ie: wasabi aioli) and extras (ie: crunch). They have a great variety of drinks on the menu, from bubble milk teas to fruity green teas. If you still have room in your belly, try an egg waffle sundae, with your choice of egg waffle, ice cream and toppings.
